LOCUS       enterokinase_sit           5 aa            linear   UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  Enterokinase (enteropeptidase) recognition/cleavage site DDDDK — a
            5-residue protease site used to remove an N-terminal fusion tag,
            leaving no extra residues on the downstream protein..
