FEATURES             Location/Qualifiers
     protein_domain  1..5
                     /label="enterokinase_site"
                     /synonym="enterokinase"
                     /synonym="enterokinase cleavage site"
                     /synonym="EK site"
                     /synonym="enteropeptidase site"
                     /synonym="DDDDK"
                     /note="Enterokinase (enteropeptidase) recognition/cleavage
                     site (Asp-Asp-Asp-Asp-Lys). The protease cleaves on the
                     C-terminal side of the Lys (after K), releasing a
                     downstream protein with no residual vector-derived residues
                     — hence its wide use for tag removal from fusion proteins.
                     The acidic (Asp)4 tetrad and the P1 Lys are recognized by
                     the enterokinase light-chain S1–S5 basic substrate pocket.
                     Sequence DDDDK is a 100%-identity match to residues 19–23
                     of the trypsinogen-1 activation propeptide
                     (UniProt:P00760), the canonical natural occurrence of the
                     motif. This part covers a 5-aa sub-span of that 247-aa
                     precursor (full_length_match=false), which is expected for
                     a short recognition motif and is not a sequence defect."
                     /citation=[1]
